parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive noise and vibration from the brakes can be a sign of worn-out brake pads or other brake components, which can lead to reduced braking performance and increased stopping distances.
symptoms: Loud noise from the brakes
vibration when applying the brakes
uneven brake wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS sensors can cause the ABS system to malfunction, leading to reduced braking performance and increased stopping distances.
symptoms: ABS light on the dashboard
uneven brake wear
reduced braking performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Cruise Control and Brake System Interaction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the cruise control system can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, making it difficult to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Cruise control locks up
engine accelerates unexpectedly
excessive effort required to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt to lock during an accident can lead to increased risk of injury or fatality, as the occupant may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: The seat belt does not lock or tighten during an accident
the seat belt does not restrain the occupant properly
the occupant is not held in place during an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked shoulder belt guide loop can compromise the structural integrity of the seat belt system, potentially leading to failure during an accident and increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: Cracking or breaking of the shoulder belt guide loop
reduced functionality of the seat belt system
increased risk of injury or fatality during an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission oil cooler line can cause excessive transmission fluid leakage, leading to transmission failure, loss of vehicle control, and potential accidents.
symptoms: Transmission fluid leakage
transmission failure
gears will not engage
transmission slips or hesitates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine rod bearing can cause oil to leak onto the hot catalytic converter, leading to a fire in the engine compartment, which can spread to the cabin and result in a total loss of the vehicle. This can cause accidents, injuries, or even fatalities.
symptoms: The engine suddenly stops or stalls
oil leaks onto the hot catalytic converter
a fire erupts in the engine compartment
the fire spreads to the air conditioning blower motor and into the cabin.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent stalling of the engine can cause the vehicle to lose power and mobility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle cuts off or stalls while driving
the vehicle does not move
the vehicle sometimes starts again after a few minutes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of the power door locks can cause the doors to become stuck, trapping passengers inside the vehicle, and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The door release button does not open
the doors cannot be opened from the inside
the doors must be opened from the outside.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the door hinge can cause the door to not close properly, which can lead to accidents or injuries, especially in the event of sudden stops or crashes.
symptoms: The door does not close properly
the door hinge is damaged or corroded.
